being read aloud.

00:02:56.860 --> 00:03:01.780
So Poetry Out Loud is a National
Youth Arts Program that seeks

00:03:01.780 --> 00:03:05.810
to foster the next generation of
literary readers by capitalizing

00:03:05.810 --> 00:03:10.050
on the latest trends in poetry,
recitation and performance.

00:03:10.050 --> 00:03:12.880
Poetry Out Loud encourages
high school students to learn

00:03:12.880 --> 00:03:15.630
about the classic and
contemporary poetry

00:03:15.630 --> 00:03:18.390
through memorization
and public recitation.

00:03:18.390 --> 00:03:22.430
Started in 2005 as a partnership
between the National Endowment

00:03:22.430 --> 00:03:25.820
for the Arts, the Poetry
Foundation, and the 53 state

00:03:25.820 --> 00:03:28.030
and jurisdictional
Arts Agencies,

00:03:28.030 --> 00:03:29.330
Poetry Out Loud has grown

00:03:29.330 --> 00:03:34.230
to serve more then 3.6 million
students and 55,000 teachers

00:03:34.230 --> 00:03:37.640
from 14,000 high
schools nationwide.

00:03:37.640 --> 00:03:41.270
This means that Poetry Out
Loud is in very state, D.C.,

00:03:41.270 --> 00:03:44.590
Puerto Rico, and the
U.S. Virgin Islands.

00:03:44.590 --> 00:03:48.190
This program helps students
master public speaking skills,

00:03:48.190 --> 00:03:50.350
build self-confidence,
and most importantly,

00:03:50.350 --> 00:03:52.800
discover their own
creative voice.

00:03:52.800 --> 00:03:56.360
If poetry recitation sounds a
bit dry to you, just you wait.

00:03:56.360 --> 00:03:59.580
In a few minutes you'll see the
students here on stage recite.

00:03:59.580 --> 00:04:02.920
And they're phenomenal, and I
can't wait for you to see them.

00:04:02.920 --> 00:04:05.770
So you may be wondering how
does Poetry Out Loud work.

00:04:05.770 --> 00:04:08.400
So Poetry Out Loud uses
a pyramid structure

00:04:08.400 --> 00:04:10.230
that starts in the classroom.

00:04:10.230 --> 00:04:13.960
Winners in the classroom advance
to school-wide competition,

00:04:13.960 --> 00:04:16.640
then to a regional and/or
a state final competition,

00:04:16.640 --> 00:04:21.370
and then ultimately at the
national finals which is here

00:04:21.370 --> 00:04:24.170
in Washington, D.C.
every spring.

00:04:24.170 --> 00:04:26.980
Poetry Out Loud students
are eligible for prizes

00:04:26.980 --> 00:04:28.280
at the same national levels

00:04:28.280 --> 00:04:31.000
of competition including
a $20,000 prize

00:04:31.000 --> 00:04:32.610
for the National Champion.

00:04:32.610 --> 00:04:36.320
And every year, Poetry Out
Loud awards more than $100,000

00:04:36.320 --> 00:04:37.800
in prizes and school stipends

00:04:37.800 --> 00:04:40.550
for the purchase of
poetry materials.

00:04:40.550 --> 00:04:44.300
