00:07:43.040 --> 00:07:47.970
"Degrees of Gray in
Philipsburg" by Richard Hugo.

00:07:47.970 --> 00:07:54.910
You might come here
Sunday on a whim.

00:07:54.910 --> 00:07:58.110
Say your life broke down.

00:07:58.110 --> 00:08:02.730
The last good kiss
you had was years ago.

00:08:02.730 --> 00:08:07.780
You walk these streets
laid out by the insane,

00:08:07.780 --> 00:08:15.530
past hotels that didn't last,
bars that did, the tortured try

00:08:15.530 --> 00:08:20.790
of local drivers to
accelerate their lives.

00:08:20.790 --> 00:08:24.650
Only churches are kept up.

00:08:24.650 --> 00:08:28.390
The jail turned 70 this year.

00:08:28.390 --> 00:08:34.750
The only prisoner is always
in, not knowing what he's done.

00:08:34.750 --> 00:08:42.040
The principal supporting
business now is rage.

00:08:42.040 --> 00:08:45.720
Hatred of the various
grays the mountain sends,

00:08:45.720 --> 00:08:49.650
hatred of the mill,
the Silver Bill repeal,

00:08:49.650 --> 00:08:55.280
the best-liked girls who
leave each year for Butte.

00:08:56.330 --> 00:09:03.410
One good restaurant and bars
can't wipe the boredom out.

00:09:03.410 --> 00:09:08.630
The 1907 boom, eight
going silver mines,

00:09:08.630 --> 00:09:12.030
a dance floor built
on springs --

00:09:13.490 --> 00:09:17.770
all memory resolves
itself in gaze,

00:09:17.770 --> 00:09:23.390
in panoramic green you know the
cattle eat or two stacks high

00:09:23.390 --> 00:09:28.440
above the town, two dead kilns,
the huge mill in collapse

00:09:28.440 --> 00:09:34.980
for fifty years that
won't fall finally down.

00:09:34.980 --> 00:09:40.750
Isn't this your life?

00:09:40.750 --> 00:09:44.760
That ancient kiss still
burning out your eyes?

00:09:44.760 --> 00:09:47.950
Isn't this defeat so accurate,

00:09:47.950 --> 00:09:51.740
the church bell simply
seems a pure announcement:

00:09:51.740 --> 00:09:56.870
ring and no one comes?

00:09:56.870 --> 00:10:01.330
Don't empty houses ring?

00:10:02.610 --> 00:10:09.210
Are magnesium and scorn
sufficient to support a town,

00:10:09.210 --> 00:10:18.660
not just Philipsburg, but towns
of towering blondes, good jazz,

00:10:18.660 --> 00:10:24.530
and booze the world
will never let you have

00:10:24.530 --> 00:10:29.670
until the town you
came from dies inside?

00:10:31.790 --> 00:10:36.670
Say no to yourself.

00:10:36.670 --> 00:10:41.650
The old man, twenty
when the jail was built,

00:10:41.650 --> 00:10:46.930
still laughs although
his lips collapse.

00:10:46.930 --> 00:10:54.760
Someday soon, he says, I'll
go to sleep and not wake up.

00:10:55.850 --> 00:10:59.050
You tell him no.

00:10:59.050 --> 00:11:02.010
You're talking to yourself.

00:11:02.010 --> 00:11:06.350
The car that brought
you here still runs.

00:11:06.350 --> 00:11:10.210
The money you buy lunch with,
no matter where it's mined,

00:11:10.210 --> 00:11:17.240
is silver, and the girl who
serves your food is slender

00:11:17.240 --> 00:11:20.970
and her red hair
lights the wall.

