00:11:43.040 --> 00:11:47.350
"Two Guitars" by
Victor Hernandez Cruz.

00:11:50.250 --> 00:11:54.150
Two guitars were left
in a room all alone.

00:11:54.150 --> 00:11:58.020
They sat on different
corners of the parlor.

00:11:58.020 --> 00:12:04.180
In this solitude they
started talking to each other.

00:12:04.180 --> 00:12:08.280
My strings are tight
and full of tears.

00:12:08.280 --> 00:12:10.830
The man who plays
me has no heart.

00:12:10.830 --> 00:12:12.700
I have seen it leave
out of his mouth.

00:12:12.700 --> 00:12:15.440
I have seen it melt
out of his eyes.

00:12:15.440 --> 00:12:18.080
It dives into the
pores of the earth.

00:12:18.080 --> 00:12:20.910
When they squeeze me tight
I bring down the angels

00:12:20.910 --> 00:12:22.970
who live off the chorus.

00:12:22.970 --> 00:12:28.580
The trios singing loosen organs
with melodious screwdrivers.

00:12:28.580 --> 00:12:32.220
Sentiment comes off the hinges
because a song is a mountain put

00:12:32.220 --> 00:12:36.250
into words and landscape is the
feeling that enters something

00:12:36.250 --> 00:12:38.010
so big in the harmony.

00:12:38.010 --> 00:12:42.950
We are always in danger of
blowing up with passion.

00:12:42.950 --> 00:12:50.580
The other guitar --
in 1944 New York,

00:12:50.580 --> 00:12:52.450
when the Trio Los
Ponchos started

00:12:52.450 --> 00:12:56.790
with Mexican &amp; Puerto Rican
birds, I am the one that one

00:12:56.790 --> 00:13:01.620
of them held tight like a woman.

00:13:01.620 --> 00:13:04.720
Their throats gardenia gardens.

00:13:04.720 --> 00:13:06.770
An airport for dreams.

00:13:06.770 --> 00:13:11.170
I've been in theaters
and cabarets.

00:13:11.170 --> 00:13:13.760
I played in an apartment
on 102nd Street

00:13:13.760 --> 00:13:17.060
after a baptism pregnant
with women.

00:13:17.060 --> 00:13:22.630
The men flirted and were
offered chicken soup.

00:13:22.630 --> 00:13:26.730
Echoes came out of
hallways as if from caves.

00:13:26.730 --> 00:13:28.810
Someone is opening the door now.

00:13:28.810 --> 00:13:37.160
The two guitars hushed and
there was a resonance in the air

00:13:37.160 --> 00:13:40.790
like what is left by the
last chord of a bolero.

00:13:42.270 --> 00:13:44.070
Thank you.

